p.quote: This early romantic novel of love, hate, and violence opens with scenes portraying the jubilation of the Argentine people upon hearing of Rosa's defeat at Caseros. The story centers on Blas de Aguilar, a former member of the dreaded 'Marzorca,' who, thwarted in his lust for Camila, vows vengeance and resorts to a young gambler to assist him in carrying out his sinister plans.
